Anambra State Governor, Charles Soludo, has said that Inmates in the state will soon have access to news and happenings from Nigeria and the rest of the globe.Soludo, who made this known on Monday in a brief of his activities on Sunday, disclosed that he visited the Ekwulobia Prison after his Thanksgiving Mass. The Nigerian Correctional Service (NCoS) officials led him on a tour of the facility to see the present conditions.Soludo chatted with the prisoners, the wardens and assured them that a new system would be set up, while he announced that the review and completion of all lingering trials was top priority.“I also promise that every leaking roof and damaged infrastructure shall be renovated.“We will also look into the long outstanding unavailability of power supply by providing solar devices and television sets where inmates can watch football, news, movies, religious activities and entertainment.”